<TITLE> Standard Bank opens forex branch in London </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 21 (bdnews24.com)--Standard Bank has opened its first money exchange branch in London for swift money delivery to Bangladesh. Bangladesh high commissioner to Britain M Sayeedur Rahman Khan inaugurated the branch of Standard Exchange Company, the foreign exchange wing of the bank, on Thursday, the high commission said in a press statement. "The Standard Bank Ltd authorities have pledged to reach money to any parts of Bangladesh within 48 to 72 hours," the statement said. Rahman said such institutions would serve the expatriates in the UK. The UK being the fifth largest source of foreign exchange for the country, easy and guaranteed channel of remittance is very important for Bangladesh, the high commissioner said. He hoped that the bank would guarantee smooth delivery of the remittances to Bangladesh.
